\deftab720
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 DEB = Detached Eclipsing Binary
\f1\b0 , a stellar system that provides one of the most direct and physically clean 
\f0\b distance measurements
\f1\b0  in astronomy. In the cosmological context, DEBs serve as the 
\f0\b geometric anchor for the LMC and SMC
\f1\b0  \'97 the second pillar of the SH0ES distance ladder alongside NGC 4258 and Gaia parallaxes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 What "detached eclipsing binary" actually means\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Three terms, each doing real work:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Binary
\f1\b0 : two gravitationally bound stars orbiting their common center of mass.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Eclipsing
\f1\b0 : from our line of sight the orbital plane is nearly edge-on, so each star periodically passes in front of the other, producing a characteristic dimming pattern in the light curve.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Detached
\f1\b0 : both stars are well within their Roche lobes \'97 no mass transfer, no tidal distortion, no shared envelope. Each star is a clean, isolated, spherical (or near-spherical) object whose properties can be modeled independently.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The "detached" qualifier matters enormously. 
\f0\b Semi-detached
\f1\b0  or 
\f0\b contact
\f1\b0  binaries have stars distorted into ellipsoidal or pear shapes, with surface brightness varying across the visible hemisphere \'97 modeling them is much harder and the distance precision suffers. Detached systems are clean enough to treat each star as a standard physics problem.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 The geometric distance, in one breath\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The brilliance of DEBs is that the orbital + photometric data 
\f0\b simultaneously yield each star's physical radius and surface brightness
\f1\b0 . Specifically:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 High-precision radial velocity curves
\f1\b0  of both components 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  orbital velocities 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  physical orbital separation $a$ via Kepler's third law.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Eclipse light curve modeling
\f1\b0  
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  the 
\f3\i fractional
\f1\i0  radii $R_1/a$ and $R_2/a$, plus the orbital inclination $i$.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Combining (1) and (2) 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  
\f0\b physical radii
\f1\b0  $R_1$ and $R_2$ in solar units.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Spectroscopy
\f1\b0  of each star at quadrature 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  effective temperatures and surface gravities.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Surface-brightness\'96color relation
\f1\b0  (calibrated empirically on Galactic stars with interferometric angular diameters; Pietrzy\uc0\u324 ski, Kervella, di Benedetto et al.) 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  predicts the apparent angular diameter $\\theta$ from the observed colors and reddening.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	6	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Distance
\f1\b0  falls out: $D = R / (\\theta/2)$.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 There's no standard candle anywhere in this. You're measuring a star's physical size from orbital dynamics and its angular size from its color, then dividing.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 The current LMC distance\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The state of the art is the 
\f0\b Araucaria Project
\f1\b0 's long-running campaign on LMC late-type DEBs (Pietrzy\uc0\u324 ski and collaborators, Concepci\'f3n + Warsaw + ESO). The latest result:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Pietrzy\uc0\u324 ski et al. 2019
\f1\b0  (
\f3\i Nature
\f1\i0  567, 200): $D_\{\\rm LMC\} = 49.59 \\pm 0.09 \\text\{ (stat)\} \\pm 0.54 \\text\{ (sys) kpc\}$ \'97 a 
\f0\b 1% distance
\f1\b0  to the LMC.\
This used 20 long-period (P ~ 60\'96770 days) eclipsing binaries with two G/K giant components (chosen because giants have well-calibrated SBC relations and the long periods give very precise radial velocities). The systematic uncertainty is dominated by the SBC relation calibration itself (~3% in angular diameter 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  1.5% in distance), with smaller contributions from reddening and orbital modeling.\
The corresponding distance modulus is $\\mu_\{\\rm LMC\} = 18.477 \\pm 0.026$ \'97 and this is the number that appears verbatim in essentially every modern H
\f4 \uc0\u8320 
\f1  paper that uses the LMC as an anchor.\
For the SMC, the equivalent measurement is 
\f0\b Graczyk et al. 2020
\f1\b0 : $D_\{\\rm SMC\} = 62.44 \\pm 0.81$ kpc (~2% precision), using 15 SMC DEBs.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

